## Features
- Per-player KeepInventory
- Nickname & Skin changer
- Anti-Armour-Breaking
- Server Freeze
  - Complete server lockdown: blocks movement, commands, interactions, inventory access, dropping items, mining, and placing blocks
  - Optional: Skin API Server Freeze (halts skin API requests during freeze)
- Accelerated HP regeneration + 2× food effectiveness
- Everything configurable via commands and config file

## Commands
- /unstablesmp nick <player> <nickname> — Set another player's nickname
- /unstablesmp skin <player> <skinName> — Change another player's skin
- /unstablesmp resetnick <player> — Reset a player's nickname
- /unstablesmp resetskin <player> — Reset a player's skin
- /unstablesmp randomnick <player> — Assign a random nickname to a player
- /unstablesmp randomskin <player> — Assign a random skin to a player

## Configuration
- All features configurable via both in-game commands and a plugin config file (toggle, values, permissions, lists, and defaults).

## Roadmap (suggested)
1. Core: Per-player KeepInventory, Anti-Armour-Breaking
2. Nickname & Skin system (commands + persistence)
3. Server Freeze implementation (including Skin API handling)
4. HP & food mechanics adjustments
5. Config file and full command/config parity
6. Add permissions, cooldowns, and targeted overrides

## Notes
- Design config to support per-world and per-group overrides.
- Ensure nickname/skin changes persist across reboots and are permission-gated.
